He was taken into custody in January after the victim's mother laid charges. CAPE TOWN - A George police officer has been arrested in connection with the rape of his girlfriend's daughter. The 27-year-old is facing six charges. He was taken into custody in January after the victim's mother laid charges. Police watchdog Ipid's Moses Dlamini said: “This rape apparently took place in December but was reported in January by the mother of the victim. The suspect was granted bail of R1,000.”